HEADWORD: cutaneous
<hw>cu*ta"ne*ous</hw> <pr>(k⟦usl⟧*t⟦amac⟧"n⟦esl⟧*⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>cutan⟦eacute⟧</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>cutis</ets> skin. See <er>Cuticle</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to the skin; existing on, or affecting, the skin; <as>as, a
<ex>cutaneous</ex> disease; <ex>cutaneous</ex> absorption;
<ex>cutaneous</ex> respiration; <ex>cutaneous</ex> nerves</as>; a
<ex>cutaneous</ex> infection.</def>⟦br⟧
